# Copy to `.env` in the project root (loaded by godotenv from cwd; see env.go loadDotEnv).
# Do not commit real secrets.

# --- Go ingest (main binary: `go build .` at repo root) ---
# Default archive: $LUMA_ARCHIVE_ROOT, else ../Livehouse_Archive when cwd is the repo, else ~/Livehouse_Archive.
# LUMA_ARCHIVE_ROOT=/path/to/Livehouse_Archive

# Repo root for relative brain-db and subprocess tools (optional; defaults to cwd).
# LUMA_REPO_ROOT=/path/to/Livehouse-Photography-Agent
# LIVEHOUSE_REPO_ROOT=/path/to/Livehouse-Photography-Agent

# SD + SQLite mode — prefer env over flags (do not commit real URLs or device names).
# DEVICE_ID=my_camera_or_card_id
# GALLERY_HOOK=https://example.com/api/ingest/check_new_images
# LIVEHOUSE_GALLERY_HOOK=https://example.com/api/ingest/check_new_images

# --- Qwen / DashScope (engine/culler/check_api.py critique) ---
# DASHSCOPE_API_KEY=sk-xxxxxxxx
# QWEN_BASE_URL=https://dashscope.aliyuncs.com/compatible-mode/v1

# --- Python gallery / Celery (see utils/luma_brain.py, gallery_server.py) ---
# LUMA_BRAIN_DB=/path/to/luma_brain.db
# LIVEHOUSE_INGEST_TOKEN=
# CELERY_BROKER_URL=redis://localhost:6379/0
# CELERY_RESULT_BACKEND=redis://localhost:6379/1

# Landing page on FastAPI `/` links here (browse UI). Default http://127.0.0.1:3000
# LIVEHOUSE_LAB_URL=http://127.0.0.1:3000

# --- Next.js web (see web/.env.example if present) ---
# NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE=http://127.0.0.1:8080

# --- Personal: local ComfyUI portrait cartoon (data stays on machine) ---
# LIVEHOUSE_COMFY_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8188
# LIVEHOUSE_COMFY_PORTRAIT_WORKFLOW=/path/to/your_api_workflow.json
# SD1.5 (default): configs/comfy/portrait_cartoon.yaml
# FLUX FP8: export LIVEHOUSE_PORTRAIT_CONFIG=configs/comfy/portrait_cartoon_flux.yaml
